IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE VIRGINIA ASSOCIATION OF FREE AND CHARITABLE CLINICS, INC.'S (THE ORGANIZATION) MISSION IS TO SUPPORT AND ADVOCATE FOR OUR MEMBER CLINICS SO THAT VIRGINIA'S UNDERSERVED HAVE ACCESS TO QUALITY CARE. TO THIS END, THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES EDUCATION, TRAINING, & TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE VIRGINIA ASSOCIATION OF FREE AND CHARITABLE CLINICS, INC.'S (THE ORGANIZATION) MISSION IS TO SUPPORT AND ADVOCATE FOR OUR MEMBER CLINICS SO THAT VIRGINIA'S UNDERSERVED HAVE ACCESS TO QUALITY CARE. TO THIS END, THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES EDUCATION, TRAINING, & TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE.
IRS990.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION ADMINISTERED FUNDING FROM THE COMMONWEALTH OF VIRGINIA AND MADE GRANTS TO ITS MEMBER CLINICS FOR THE PURPOSE OF PROVIDING ACCESS TO PRESCRIPTION MEDICATIONS AND HEALTHCARE SERVICES. IN ADDITION, THE ASSOCIATION ADMINISTERED ARPA FUNDING FROM THE COMMONWEALTH OF VIRGINIA FOR REIMBURSEMENT OF MEMBER CLINICS' EXPENSES FOR COVID-19 TREATMENT AND FOR INFRASTRUCTURE TO MAINTAIN & BUILD CAPACITY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION PLANNED AND CONDUCTED AN ANNUAL CONFERENCE OF VIRGINIA'S FREE AND CHARITABLE CLINICS, A LEADERSHIP CONFERENCE FOR EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS OF MEMBER CLINICS, AND EDUCATIONAL WORKSHOPS, WEBINARS, AND TELECONFERENCES ON TOPICS SUCH AS EXPANDING CARE, HR, FUND DEVELOPMENT, SOCIAL DETERMINANTS OF HEALTH, AND VALUE DRIVEN CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: THIS CATEGORY INCLUDES ALL OTHER UNALLOCATED PROGRAM EXPENSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION FOLLOWS GENERALLY ACCEPTED ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES REGARDING "ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS". THIS ACCOUNTING STANDARD PROVIDES DETAILED GUIDANCE FOR FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION, MEASUREMENT, AND DISCLOSURE OF UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS RECOGNIZED IN THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. IT REQUIRES AN ENTITY TO RECOGNIZE THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT IMPACT OF A TAX POSITION WHEN IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE POSITION WILL NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION. THE TAX YEARS 2020 TO 2022 REMAIN SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES. THE ORGANIZATION INCLUDES PENALTIES AND INTEREST ASSESSED BY INCOME TAXING AUTHORITIES IN OPERATING EXPENSES. NO PENALTIES OR INTEREST WERE INCURRED FOR THE YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2023 AND 2022 .

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A FORMAL "FUNDS-ACCREDITATION-MEMBERSHIP" COMMITTEE WHICH MAINTAINS RESPONSIBLITIES FOR REVIEW OF MEMBERSHIP APPLICATIONS, CONDUCTING ON-SITE VISITS TO MEMBERSHIP APPLICANTS AND MAKING RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE BOARD FOR ACTION ON MEMBERSHIP APPLICATIONS. THE COMMITTEE IS RESPONSIBLE FOR MONITORING INTERIM AND FINAL PROGRESS REPORTS FOR STATE FUNDS WHEN/IF THE ORGANIZATION DETERMINES THERE MAY BE QUESTIONABLE OR ERRONEOUS DATA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION DISTRIBUTES THE FORM 990 TO THE AUDIT AND FINANCE COMMITTEE AND TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS. BOARD MINUTES REFLECT THAT THE BOARD HAS RECEIVED AND ACCEPTED THE AUDIT AND FORM 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A WRITTEN "CONFLICT OF INTEREST" POLICY WHICH IS REAFFIRMED EACH JANUARY. EACH BOARD MEMBER COMPLETES A CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORM AND SIGNS THE FORM IN JANUARY. THE FORMS ARE MAINTAINED ON FILE IN THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION POSTS ITS CURRENT AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENT ON ITS WEB SITE AND ON WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG , EACH YEAR. IN ADDITION, AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE POSTED TO THE MEMBER CENTER ON THE WEBSITE. IT IS THE POLICY OF THE ORGANIZATION TO PROVIDE COPIES OF FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFICT OF INTEREST INFORMATION AND OTHER DOCUMENTS TO THE MEMBERS OF THE PUBLIC UPON WRITTEN REQUEST. SINGLE COPIES ARE PROVIDED FREE OF CHARGE. MULTIPLE COPIES ARE SENT UPON THE RECEIPT OF FIFTY CENTS FOR EACH PAGE REQUESTED. THESE REQUESTS ARE PROCESSED AND THE INFORMATION IS FORWARDED WITHIN TWO WEEKS.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
